Spec: SpecDD CLI Application
Platform: TypeScript/Node.js/ESM
Purpose:
  Provide a command-line tool that supports SpecDD workflows.

Structure:
  ../README.md: User-facing CLI usage documentation.
  ./main.ts: CLI entrypoint source emitted as main.js.
  ./main.sdd: CLI entrypoint specification.
  ./cli-error.ts: Shared base class for expected CLI-facing errors.
  ./cli-error.sdd: Shared CLI error specification.
  ./constants.ts: Shared constants for paths, URLs, asset names, and common CLI text.
  ./constants.sdd: Shared constants specification.
  ./container.ts: Application container for explicit service wiring.
  ./container.sdd: Application container specification.
  ./commands: CLI command handlers.
  ./infrastructure: Runtime adapters for platform APIs.
  ./infrastructure/*.sdd: Infrastructure adapter specification.
  ./services: Application services, with each service in its own directory.
  ./services/agentskills: Agent Skills deployment service.
  ./services/*/service.sdd: Service specification.
  ./services/bootstrap-metadata: Shared bootstrap metadata service.
  ./services/config: Shared configuration service.
  ./services/logger: Shared CLI notice logger service.
  ./services/specdd-version: Shared SpecDD version service.
  ./**/*.test.ts: Jest test suites.
  ./types: Local TypeScript declaration shims.
  ./types/*.sdd: Local TypeScript declaration shim specifications.

Owns:
  ./

Can modify:
  ./**
  ../README.md

Can read:
  ../README.md
  ../package.json
  ../.specdd/*

Must:
  Use TypeScript targeting the Node.js runtime declared by ../package.json.
  Expose a CLI named specdd.
  Build shared service instances through @Container.
  Keep command parsing separate from application services.
  Route command behavior through services.
  Let commands access services through @Container.
  Support init, update, check-update, and agentskills deploy commands.
  Keep shared paths, URLs, asset names, and common CLI text in ./constants.ts.
  Keep ../README.md up to date when adding, changing, or removing CLI commands, options, defaults, or user-visible command safety behavior.
  Report filesystem changes clearly.
  Route service-originated CLI notices through the logger service.
  Fully test and cover each function, service, and command with tests.

Depends on:
  Node.js
  TypeScript
  commander
  fast-glob
  zod
  chalk
  openpgp
  jszip
  jest

Exposes:
  specdd CLI
  specdd init
  specdd update
  specdd check-update
  specdd agentskills deploy
